# App Shell Layout Pattern

Use this structure for any web app with a sidebar + main content area. It solves the most common layout bugs: tiny/invisible toggles, sidebars that can't be re-opened, header elements floating on top of content, and theme/utility controls drifting around the corner.

## Page Structure (the only correct order)

```
<div class="flex flex-col h-screen overflow-hidden">

  <header class="flex-shrink-0 h-14 flex items-stretch border-b z-20">
    [ sidebar-toggle ]   [ brand ]   [ primary nav (flex-1) ]   [ utility cluster (theme, user, etc.) ]
  </header>

  <div class="flex flex-1 overflow-hidden">
    <aside class="flex-shrink-0 transition-[width] {open ? w-64 : w-0} overflow-hidden">
      <div class="w-64 h-full overflow-y-auto"> {sidebar} </div>
    </aside>
    <main class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto"> {children} </main>
  </div>

</div>
```

### Non-negotiable rules

1. **Root is `flex-col h-screen overflow-hidden`.** Header + body row are siblings; never overlap them with `absolute`.
2. **Header is `flex-shrink-0` with a fixed height** (56px / `h-14` is the default). It owns z-index `z-20`.
3. **Body row is `flex flex-1 overflow-hidden`.** Sidebar and main scroll independently inside.
4. **Sidebar is collapsed via width**, not display. Animate `transition-[width]`. Collapsed = `w-0`, expanded = `w-64`.
5. **Inner sidebar content has a fixed `w-64`** so it doesn't reflow during the collapse animation.
6. **Main uses `flex-1 overflow-y-auto`** — never set its width manually.

## The Sidebar Toggle (the bug this rule exists for)

The toggle button MUST live in the header, NOT inside the sidebar. If it lives in the sidebar, it disappears when collapsed and the user is stranded.

### Required toggle properties

- Lives in the header bar, leftmost slot.
- Hit target ≥ 40×40 px (44×44 preferred, 56×56 for desktop apps with a tall header).
- Has a visible icon (hamburger, chevron, or animated morph between the two).
- Has `aria-label`, `aria-expanded`, and a `title` tooltip.
- Hover state changes color/background — never a "ghost" 5×5 button.

### Reference implementation (React + Tailwind)

```tsx
<button
  onClick={() => setOpen(v => !v)}
  title={open ? "Collapse sidebar" : "Expand sidebar"}
  aria-label={open ? "Collapse sidebar" : "Expand sidebar"}
  aria-expanded={open}
  className="w-14 h-full flex items-center justify-center border-r
             text-muted hover:text-accent hover:bg-accent/5 transition-colors"
>
  <span className="relative w-5 h-5 flex flex-col justify-center items-center gap-[3px]">
    <span className={`block h-[2px] bg-current rounded-full transition-all duration-200
                      ${open ? "w-3 -translate-x-1 -rotate-45 translate-y-[5px]" : "w-5"}`} />
    <span className="block h-[2px] w-5 bg-current rounded-full transition-all duration-200" />
    <span className={`block h-[2px] bg-current rounded-full transition-all duration-200
                      ${open ? "w-3 -translate-x-1 rotate-45 -translate-y-[5px]" : "w-5"}`} />
  </span>
</button>
```

## Header Slot Conventions

| Slot                | Purpose                                  | Width      |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| Toggle              | Collapse/expand sidebar                  | 56 px      |
| Brand               | App name/logo, monospace OK              | auto       |
| Primary nav         | Top-level routes (Browse / Stats / etc.) | `flex-1`   |
| Utility cluster     | Theme picker, user menu, settings        | auto, with `border-l` separator |

- Active nav item: subtle accent underline (`absolute bottom-0 h-px bg-accent`), not a filled pill.
- Utility controls (theme picker, etc.) MUST be inline children of the header. Never `position: absolute` floating in a corner — they overlap content and cause the exact "elements in wrong place" bug.
- Dropdowns from utility buttons: `position: absolute` relative to the button, anchored to the correct edge (`right-0` for right-side controls).

## Sidebar Conventions

- Sidebar = filtering and secondary navigation only. Primary nav lives in the header.
- Section labels: `text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]` font-mono for terminal aesthetic, or `text-xs uppercase tracking-wider` for a softer look.
- Each section divided by `border-b`.
- Tags/chips wrap with `flex flex-wrap gap-1`.

## Common Bugs This Pattern Prevents

| Bug                                                          | Cause                                       | Fix                                                  |
| ------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Sidebar can't be reopened after collapse                     | Toggle lives inside sidebar                 | Move toggle to header                                |
| Toggle is invisible / 5×5 ghost button                       | Tiny size + no border/bg                    | ≥ 40×40, hover state, visible icon                   |
| Theme/utility button overlaps brand or content               | `absolute top-2 left-2`                     | Make it an inline header child                       |
| Sidebar collapse leaves a 40px stub                          | `w-10` instead of `w-0` when collapsed      | Use `w-0` and put toggle elsewhere                   |
| Content reflows mid-animation                                | Sidebar inner content uses `w-full`         | Inner uses fixed `w-64`, parent animates width       |
| Header scrolls with content                                  | Header inside the scroll container          | Header is sibling of body row, `flex-shrink-0`       |
| Dropdown menu clips off-screen                               | Anchored to wrong edge                      | `right-0` for right-side, `left-0` for left-side     |

## When This Rule Applies

Apply when building or refactoring any app that has:
- A sidebar (collapsible or not)
- A top header / nav bar
- Multiple top-level views/routes
- Sizing, positioning, or "element disappears" complaints
